    <stitle>MULTI-LINK FRONT AIR SUSPENSION - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - SHOCK ABSORBER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SHOCK ABSORBER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Shock Absorber - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0301511" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301511.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Shock Mounting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SHOCK ABSORBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TOP MOUNT BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FRAME MOUNT BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BOTTOM MOUNT BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. AXLE MOUNT BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow these steps to exhaust air from the vehicle and suspension system:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Drain air from vehicle reservoirs.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove bolt, washer, nut, and height control rod from the valve lever (
                        <hotlnk document="s03015_10.xml" xrefid="f0301507">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Rotate the valve lever on the height control valve to EXH (exhaust) position to
                        drain air from system (
                        <hotlnk document="s03015_10.xml" xrefid="f0301507">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bottom mount bolt and nut from the shock absorber and axle mount bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the top mount bolt and nut from the shock absorber and frame mount bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shock absorber.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Shock Absorber - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the shock absorber on the frame mount bracket and install the top mount bolt
                    and nut (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301511">Figure 13</hotlnk>). Do not tighten at this time.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When installing the bottom mount bolt for the shock, be sure to attach the support bracket for
                        the height control rod (
                        <hotlnk document="s03015_11.xml" xrefid="f0301527">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the shock absorber on the axle mount bracket and install the bottom mount bolt
                    and nut (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301511">Figure 13</hotlnk>). Torque bolt to 250 to 300 lbf-ft (339 to 407 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque the top mount bolt to 195 to 240 lbf-ft (265 to 325 N&#8226;m).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
